             was indicted for <rs id="t18211205-28-off163" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-off163" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-off163" type="offenceSubcategory" value="embezzlement"></interp>
               embezzlement
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
            
               
                  <persName id="t18211205-28-victim327" type="victimName">
                     BENJAMIN ROBERT 
                     ROSE
                  <interp inst="t18211205-28-victim327" type="surname" value="ROSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-victim327" type="given" value="BENJAMIN ROBERT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-victim327" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-28-off163 t18211205-28-victim327"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            . I am an <rs id="t18211205-28-viclabel164" type="occupation">oilman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-28-victim327 t18211205-28-viclabel164"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18211205-28-crimeloc165">Cheapside</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-28-crimeloc165" type="placeName" value="Cheapside"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-28-crimeloc165" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-28-off163 t18211205-28-crimeloc165"></join>. The prisoner was my <rs id="t18211205-28-deflabel166" type="occupation">porter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-28-defend325 t18211205-28-deflabel166"></join>, and entrusted to receive money for me. Mr. Kerridge was a customer of mine, and owed me 2 l. 5 s., I had not directed the prisoner to apply for it - it was for two parcels of goods, the first parcel was delivered eight or nine days before. He lived about six weeks with me - I had a good character with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-28-person328">
                  GEORGE 
                  KERRIDGE
               <interp inst="t18211205-28-person328" type="surname" value="KERRIDGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-person328" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-person328" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep the Bedford Arms, public-house, in South-street, Manchester-square, and deal with Mr. Rose, I owed him 2 l. 5 s., I generally pay as the goods come in. On Thursday, the 29th of November, the prisoner brought some oil; the previous quantity had not been paid<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182112050017"></xptr>for - I desired my wife to pay him for it, and I saw her give him two sovereigns, and 5 s. in silver; I saw Mr. Rose a few days after, and told him I had paid the prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-28-person329">
                  BENJAMIN 
                  ROBERT ROSE
               <interp inst="t18211205-28-person329" type="surname" value="ROBERT ROSE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-person329" type="given" value="BENJAMIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-person329" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             re-examined. He should have given me the money immediately on his coming home, he never accounted to me for it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-28-person330">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SHEPPARD
               <interp inst="t18211205-28-person330" type="surname" value="SHEPPARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-person330" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18211205-28-person330" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I apprehended him at his master's, on the 1st of December, he said nothing.</p>
               <p>The prisoner begged for mercy.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18211205-28-verdict167" type="verdictDescription">
